# Build Phases

Build this app in small, testable phases.

Do not attempt to build every feature at once.

Each phase should produce a working app state before moving to the next phase.

## Phase 1: Navigation Skeleton

Goal: Prove the app structure and navigation.

Build:

* Android project setup
* Kotlin
* Jetpack Compose
* Material 3
* Home screen
* Top-right plus button
* Placeholder list of log cards
* Right-side plus button on each log card
* Navigation routes:

  * Home
  * Create/Edit Log System
  * Entry List
  * New Entry

Required behavior:

* Top-right plus opens Create/Edit Log System screen.
* Tapping a log card opens Entry List screen.
* Tapping the right-side plus on a log card opens New Entry screen.
* New Entry screen is full-screen, not a dialog.

No database required yet. Placeholder data is acceptable in this phase.

## Phase 2: Local Database for Log Systems

Goal: Save custom log systems locally.

Build:

* Room database
* LogTemplate entity
* DAO for creating, reading, updating, deleting log templates
* Repository layer if useful
* Home screen loads log systems from database
* Create/Edit Log System screen saves a real log template

Fields for LogTemplate:

* id
* name
* description
* createdAt
* updatedAt
* schemaJson

Manual field editing can be minimal at this phase.

## Phase 3: Manual Custom Fields

Goal: Allow the user to define fields for a log system.

Supported field types:

* text
* single choice
* multiple choice
* scale 1 to 5
* date
* time
* datetime
* yes/no

Build:

* Field creation UI
* Add/remove/reorder fields
* Save fields into schemaJson
* Preview generated form if practical

Do not add Form Markdown yet.

## Phase 4: Dynamic Entry Forms

Goal: Generate entry forms from each log system.

Build:

* LogEntry entity
* DAO for creating, reading, updating, deleting entries
* New Entry screen generated from schemaJson
* Save entries as valuesJson
* Auto-created timestamp
* Entry List screen shows saved entries in reverse chronological order
* Entry Detail/Edit screen if needed

Fields for LogEntry:

* id
* templateId
* createdAt
* updatedAt
* valuesJson

Required behavior:

* Tapping the right-side plus on a log card opens a generated full-screen form.
* Saving the form creates a LogEntry.
* Tapping a log card opens the list of entries for that log.

## Phase 5: Readable Report Export

Goal: Export a human-readable report for one log.

Build:

* Export button on Entry List screen
* Markdown export for one log
* Plain text export for one log
* Android share/save intent

Report should include:

* Log name
* Date range
* Total entries
* Counts by severity if a severity field exists
* Counts by common choice fields if practical
* Entries listed vertically, field by field
* Notes displayed as block text

CSV is not required in this phase.

PDF is not required in this phase.

## Phase 6: JSON Backup and Restore

Goal: Protect all app data.

Build:

* Backup all data as JSON
* Restore all data from JSON
* Include all log templates
* Include all log entries
* Include schemaJson for each log system
* Add backup/restore option in a menu or backup screen

JSON is for backup and restore, not normal sharing.

## Phase 7: Form Markdown Import

Goal: Let the user paste a structured Markdown-like template to create a log system.

Supported format:

# Log Name

## Field Label

type: single

* Option A
* Option B

## Field Label

type: multiple

* Option A
* Option B

## Severity

type: scale
min: 1
max: 5

## Notes

type: text

Build:

* Paste Form Markdown screen
* Parser that converts Form Markdown into schemaJson
* Preview generated fields before saving
* Store original Form Markdown if desired

Do not make this parser more complex than necessary.

## Phase 8: CSV Export

Goal: Provide spreadsheet-compatible export.

Build:

* Export one log as CSV
* Export all logs as separate CSV files if practical
* Multiple-choice values can be joined with semicolons
* Notes should be quoted safely
* CSV is secondary and not the main readable format

Each log should export separately because different logs can have different fields.

## Phase 9: PDF Export

Goal: Provide polished readable reports.

Build:

* Convert readable report to PDF
* Use one-column layout first
* Consider two-column layout only later
* Keep notes readable
* Avoid cramped table layouts

PDF export should be based on the readable report, not the CSV.

## Worklog Requirement

After every meaningful coding session or agent run, update:

docs/CHANGELOG_WORKLOG.md

Each entry should include:

* Date
* Summary
* Changed
* Added
* Fixed
* Notes
* Next steps
* Known issues

Do not leave the worklog vague. It should be useful to a future coding agent and to the user.
